Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.85,0:01:51.91,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear cats meowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.27,0:02:02.51,Magus-Flashback,Cat lady,0000,0000,0000,,Say, you cats have nine lives, do you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.68,0:02:09.09,Magus-Flashback,Cat lady,0000,0000,0000,,Since you have so many, \Nwhy not spare one for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.19,0:02:30.40,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.78,0:02:35.33,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.23,0:02:39.15,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,G-Good morning, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.15,0:02:40.58,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You gave me a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.58,0:02:44.49,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,One moment you collapsed, \Nthe next, you'd fallen asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.49,0:02:45.97,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.03,0:02:49.49,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Was I {\i0}that{\i1} tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.42,0:03:10.49,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.90,0:03:13.97,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,It's the train to our next \Nhoneymoon destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.02,0:03:17.04,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.50,0:03:26.59,Default,Sealion,0000,0000,0000,,There is a messenger here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.35,0:03:28.82,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Bring them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.75,0:03:36.64,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,This train is not meant for humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.25,0:03:40.33,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.83,0:03:44.11,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,Pleased to meet you, sir mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.68,0:03:46.55,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Word travels fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.55,0:03:50.43,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,Rumors spread a hundred miles \Na day in the cat world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.78,0:03:52.18,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He spoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:55.17,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps that would be surprising for \Na cat on its first or second life,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.17,0:03:58.50,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,but this is my seventh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:00.96,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,There would be something \Nwrong with me if I couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.26,0:04:03.81,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,First? Seventh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.14,0:04:06.04,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.04,0:04:08.97,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Cats have nine lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.33,0:04:11.62,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Nine lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.62,0:04:13.68,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.53,0:04:18.42,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,We cats become wiser with each life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.05,0:04:22.94,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,We too have the idea of "countries" and "kings."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.49,0:04:30.35,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,Our King of Cats awaits at Ulthar, sir mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.81,0:05:11.64,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,There are a lot of cats here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.30,0:05:14.70,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's the Kingdom of Cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.00,0:05:17.17,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,Here, there have historically \Nbeen many cat lovers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.17,0:05:19.84,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,and none who are cruel to us, \Nso naturally, our numbers grew.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.22,0:05:23.85,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,There are some other\N reasons as well, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.93,0:05:30.75,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,Barney! Where the heck have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.11,0:05:35.65,Default,Top one percent of the bottom quintile,0000,0000,0000,,The King wanted me to take a look, \Nso I was on patrol, Jasper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.98,0:05:40.72,Default,Top one percent of the bottom quintile,0000,0000,0000,,You have a scent that takes me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.18,0:05:44.15,Default,Top one percent of the bottom quintile,0000,0000,0000,,You smell kind of like the mages\N that I used to see around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.93,0:05:47.10,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,What an overly chatty animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.36,0:05:51.47,Default,Of one-eighth of median income,0000,0000,0000,,Shut it, you prickly Thorn Mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.47,0:05:54.79,Default,Of one-eighth of median income,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to scratch up \Nyour bride, so don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.42,0:05:57.49,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Even {\i1}cats{\i0} know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.43,0:06:01.20,Default,Of global gross GDP is less than half,0000,0000,0000,,Cats' rumors can easily make it \Nto the other side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.02,0:06:27.09,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,She just looked at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.31,0:06:33.54,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. Where's this King?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.98,0:06:35.78,Default,Nyan,0000,0000,0000,,Right next to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.58,0:06:45.32,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, mage and apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.71,0:06:48.63,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You're the King of Cats?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.84,0:06:49.90,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.90,0:06:52.38,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Molly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.38,0:06:54.38,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,You must be Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.63,0:06:59.85,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,You struck me as odd, choosing to \Npair bond with this cranky man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.85,0:07:01.35,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.35,0:07:02.70,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Pair bond...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.70,0:07:05.04,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to see you both here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.04,0:07:08.24,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what I would have done \Nif they'd sent a sorcerer instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:10.53,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Would it have been bad if we were sorcerers?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.37,0:07:14.61,Default,Twenty percent of children under thirty-four,0000,0000,0000,,We hate sorcerers, lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.61,0:07:17.41,Default,Twenty percent of children under thirty-four,0000,0000,0000,,They're skeevy, lawless lowlifes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.41,0:07:19.08,Default,Twenty percent of children under thirty-four,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna be anywhere near them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.14,0:07:23.99,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,I know you were sent here by the Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.25,0:07:28.63,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could tell you that there \Nwas nothing wrong with our land.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.77,0:07:32.27,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,However, we're in a bit of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:35.93,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,You'll help us, right, mage?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.36,0:07:39.64,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm here, \Nalthough I wish I weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.76,0:07:42.13,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, who are you, miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.89,0:07:45.46,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,E-Elias...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.46,0:07:49.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Who were you talking to outside my house?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.62,0:07:57.60,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. I just noticed \Nthe cute cat on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.60,0:07:59.61,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's our cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.01,0:08:01.79,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she pretty?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.11,0:08:06.69,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Molly, it'll be time to eat soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.69,0:08:08.60,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Come inside, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.09,0:08:13.81,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,My owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.81,0:08:17.55,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,I've looked after her since she \Nwas born, so she's like my child.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.89,0:08:21.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,She's a cute girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.63,0:08:23.50,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,I'm proud of her like she's my own daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.13,0:08:28.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.55,0:08:30.79,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I hate kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.78,0:08:32.28,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,They don't even have magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.28,0:08:35.11,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,but they have a strong ability \Nto perceive the essence of a being.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.11,0:08:37.32,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, they can see through me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.83,0:08:40.57,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I might as well go investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.50,0:08:44.36,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.83,0:08:47.38,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Something doesn't feel right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.22,0:08:52.32,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then, I'd like to show you around.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.91,0:09:23.41,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago—so long ago that even we, with our \Nnine lives, don't have many tales to tell of it—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.16,0:09:29.79,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,there was a man here who enjoyed killing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.30,0:09:31.75,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Killing cats?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.62,0:09:36.02,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,Run as we may, hide as we may,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.02,0:09:40.18,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,we were captured,\Nand our lives were snuffed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.04,0:09:52.69,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,It was the first King of \NCats who ended that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.08,0:09:58.14,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,The first king gathered the remaining\N cats, and together they attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:02.83,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,They clawed him apart, chewed \Nhim to bits, drank his blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.83,0:10:05.16,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,and left not even a trace of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.63,0:10:15.26,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,Each generation of kings pays for\Nthe reverence we receive by sacrificing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.26,0:10:18.18,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,several of our lives in \Norder to hold the corruption at bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.18,0:10:21.05,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,That's the price we pay for our veneration.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.84,0:10:26.15,Default,Income disparity of market value deflation,0000,0000,0000,,Look really carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.15,0:10:28.34,Default,Income disparity of market value deflation,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.03,0:10:46.81,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,It's filth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.28,0:10:49.89,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,The corrupt state of souls \Nthat were never cleansed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.44,0:10:54.24,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,The corruption has been trying \Nto escape in recent days.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.34,0:11:01.64,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,It seeks maniacally and indiscriminately\N to take the lives of both cats and humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.89,0:11:06.39,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,I must not allow it to emerge,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.39,0:11:08.26,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,even if it kills me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.28,0:11:14.35,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,For the girl's sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.90,0:11:17.77,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,What mother fails to protect her own child?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.17,0:11:21.78,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,It would be unthinkable, at least to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:29.28,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.05,0:11:35.17,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.02,0:11:43.21,Default,Yellow,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take this personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.96,0:12:13.11,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Mina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.69,0:12:14.66,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Mina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.76,0:12:18.76,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Mina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.58,0:12:20.66,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Matthew.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.42,0:12:22.83,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home, Mina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.12,0:12:25.59,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you be in bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.94,0:12:28.50,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine, Matthew.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:29.85,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.42,0:12:31.42,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.42,0:12:34.16,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,There were lots of them \Nblooming by the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.16,0:12:35.48,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.62,0:12:37.93,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.40,0:12:42.45,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,How's your fever?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.12,0:12:45.38,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,You're still burning up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.59,0:12:49.69,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.78,0:12:51.88,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Shoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.88,0:12:54.50,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Get off your butt and go catch \Nsome mice or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.46,0:12:57.02,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,What's his problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.02,0:13:00.13,Magus-Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,That cat seriously only likes you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.46,0:13:06.91,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I heard there's a wandering \Nsorcerer in town right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.44,0:13:11.35,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask if they have any good medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.04,0:13:14.12,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.12,0:13:16.51,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I always do this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.51,0:13:18.73,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.35,0:13:25.45,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,You've always been prone to sickness, \Nbut I knew that when we got together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.65,0:13:29.99,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Now, get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.36,0:13:34.56,Magus-Flashback,Cat Dad,0000,0000,0000,,You better not be knitting \Nsocks or coats like last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.56,0:13:35.87,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.73,0:13:39.13,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,See you soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.47,0:13:59.43,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,If only I had nine lives, like a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.08,0:14:07.93,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,This was my sin,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.09,0:14:13.94,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,and my punishment for resting \Nmy laurels on his love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.49,0:14:15.86,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.30,0:14:20.58,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you could say I'm the \Ncore of this corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.84,0:14:21.49,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Core?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.03,0:14:26.26,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,This man is affixed to me. He won't let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.69,0:14:31.92,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault that he's become\N such an abomination.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.81,0:14:39.98,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,This man...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.93,0:14:41.81,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Matthew.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.99,0:14:44.77,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,My husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:52.06,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:53.86,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,For his sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.47,0:14:55.48,Default,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,and mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.48,0:14:58.12,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I don't know anything yet—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.58,0:15:04.31,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.24,0:15:06.09,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.61,0:15:08.52,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.11,0:15:12.72,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.43,0:15:15.04,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I didn't come sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.07,0:15:21.33,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.33,0:15:22.66,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Can you breathe?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.66,0:15:23.80,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:27.21,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the one who \Nthrew Chise into the pond?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.21,0:15:29.73,Default,Two-fifths of the Bread and Cake,0000,0000,0000,,She gave off a flash and vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.73,0:15:34.16,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,There was magic residue all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:38.68,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like someone's \Ntrying to get in our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.52,0:15:43.51,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to give you time to rest,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.00,0:15:47.55,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,but Chise, I have a task for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.11,0:15:49.21,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,For me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.83,0:15:52.88,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,We need to do something about {\i1}that{\i0}, soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.19,0:15:55.29,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to cleanse it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.92,0:16:00.59,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Containing it only delays \Nthe inevitable problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.59,0:16:04.91,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need the magic to contain \Nit, but magic to cleanse it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.91,0:16:06.92,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Magic to cleanse it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.92,0:16:10.81,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't had you practice \Nmagic properly yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.66,0:16:14.52,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,But I believe you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.05,0:16:20.78,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,If I can't, will he lose faith in me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.59,0:16:27.21,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,If you think I can,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.63,0:16:29.54,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:34.34,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You heard her, King of Cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.58,0:16:35.95,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.95,0:16:38.64,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,I'll clear the place of \Nas many people as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.26,0:16:41.51,Default,Mop,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.51,0:16:42.71,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.47,0:16:45.91,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,At night, then, when \Nthere aren't any people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.69,0:16:57.90,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,This is a mantle purified with snowmelt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.02,0:17:02.11,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,We use frankincense in the censer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.63,0:17:05.62,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Let's use a branch of gorse \Nin place of a staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.95,0:17:12.95,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You would normally need \Nyour own chant and staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.95,0:17:14.65,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll have to make do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.17,0:17:17.55,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,Is your lecture going to take a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.33,0:17:19.64,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,An ariel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.64,0:17:21.79,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.05,0:17:24.79,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be a great help for our task today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.16,0:17:28.51,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Although I don't look forward to it, \Nespecially after what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.26,0:17:33.98,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,Cleansing and extinguishing \Nis what we're good at.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.34,0:17:36.84,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,The wind clears away everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.20,0:17:39.48,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,Meat, bone, even trees and boulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.48,0:17:41.02,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,We weather it all away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.02,0:17:46.31,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,So we're the best ones for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.98,0:17:51.25,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, why is it me and not you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.88,0:17:57.18,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to admit it, but I'm not \Ngood at this kind of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.18,0:17:59.34,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,My essence is shadow, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.23,0:18:02.04,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not compatible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.19,0:18:07.89,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.93,0:18:12.97,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,All you have to do is picture it in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.71,0:18:19.13,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Just wish for it to disappear, \Nlike a spring wind
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.13,0:18:21.73,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,blowing away the cold winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.35,0:18:25.15,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,The ariels will guide you from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:26.88,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.03,0:18:31.29,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, love the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.51,0:18:36.66,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,The world you lived in may \Nnot have been your ally.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.99,0:18:38.47,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,But it wasn't your enemy, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:42.59,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Your key is already in the silver lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.34,0:18:45.30,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left to do is to open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.87,0:18:55.39,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Then again, that's just something \Nsomeone once told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:04.23,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Do you love this place, Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.92,0:19:10.08,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.48,0:19:41.89,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Will he lose faith in me if I fail?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.76,0:19:43.51,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.99,0:19:48.25,Magus-Flashback,Cat Mom,0000,0000,0000,,For his sake, and mine, kill us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.46,0:19:54.38,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,How could she say that \Nwith such a calm voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.28,0:20:00.50,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,How did they end up the way they did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.92,0:20:14.38,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.38,0:20:15.72,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,Stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.84,0:20:28.61,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Do I have to wipe them out?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.92,0:20:33.06,Default,Yellow,0000,0000,0000,,I'd appreciate it if you wouldn't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.06,0:20:34.36,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You're from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.08,0:20:36.23,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Ariel!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.28,0:20:42.15,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, we have a use for that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.15,0:20:43.92,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,We can't let you get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.42,0:20:48.17,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder I smelled something unfamiliar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.43,0:20:50.68,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Renfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.84,0:20:54.97,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you remember my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.13,0:20:58.27,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like you take good care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.80,0:21:07.11,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because she's your precious \Ntest subject, Pilum Murialis?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.80,0:21:09.45,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Test subject?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.71,0:21:13.07,Default,Ariel,0000,0000,0000,,Chise! Don't listen to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.37,0:21:17.04,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,This glove is made of iron fibers, \Nwhich you hate so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.35,0:21:19.06,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,Squirm, and you'll get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.55,0:21:20.62,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Ariel!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.62,0:21:22.80,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Why would a mage do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.80,0:21:24.39,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,Mage?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.86,0:21:26.91,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,You're mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.91,0:21:28.77,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a sorcerer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.48,0:21:30.94,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,Poor girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.94,0:21:33.30,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,Even the fairies are deceiving you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.13,0:21:35.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Deceiving me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.51,0:21:38.30,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,She isn't deceiving you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.63,0:21:40.81,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,We detest lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.09,0:21:42.60,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.60,0:21:45.74,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,All you do is conceal the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.72,0:21:52.63,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,That's how you put this \Nunfortunate child on a leash,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.63,0:21:55.61,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,to try to use her to satisfy \Nyour own curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.63,0:22:01.01,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you tell her of the \Nfate that awaits a Sleigh Beggy?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.20,0:22:07.67,Default,Awesome hair,0000,0000,0000,,Of the death that will soon come to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.38,0:22:16.60,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Death?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.96,0:22:21.30,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,My death?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.64,0:23:59.33,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The girl's heart is rocked by the \Ntruth with which she is confronted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.33,0:24:01.33,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Will the despairing child's decision
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.33,0:24:05.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,bring an end to the tragic obsession \Nlurking deep in the Kingdom of Cats?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.21,0:24:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't look inside!
